250 g Salmon Fillets, skin-on
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
1 tbsp Enchilada Spice Blend
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
1 unit(s) Lime
7 g Cilantro
113 g Red Cabbage, shredded
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
2 tbsp Chipotle Sauce
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Zest, then juice half the lime (whole lime for 4 ppl). Cut remaining lime into wedges.
Roughly chop cilantro.
Pat salmon dry with paper towels, then season with salt, Enchilada Spice Blend and pepper.

Stir together sour cream, lime zest, lime juice and 1 tsp (2 tsp) garlic in a large bowl. ( NOTE: Reference garlic guide.)

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then salmon.
Pan-fry until golden-brown and cooked through, 3-5 min per side.**

Meanwhile, add cabbage and half the cilantro to the large bowl with slaw dressing.
Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine.

Wrap tortillas in paper towels.
Microwave until warm and flexible, 1 min. (TIP: You can skip this step if you don't want to warm the tortillas!)

Divide slaw between tortillas, then top with salmon.
Drizzle chipotle sauce over top, then sprinkle with feta and remaining cilantro.
Squeeze a lime wedge over top, if desired.

If you've opted to get salmon, prep in the same way the recipe instructs you to prep the shrimp, then, then season with salt, Enchilada Spice Blend and pepper.

P an-fry salmon until golden-brown and cooked through, 3-5 min per side.**

